  <h1>Privacy Policy – Azimuth Finder</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 20, 2025</p>

  <p>Azimuth Finder respects your privacy. This app is designed to work completely offline and does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.</p>

  <h2>📡 Data Collection</h2>
  <p>Azimuth Finder does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Personal information</li>
    <li>Location data</li>
    <li>Device information</li>
    <li>Usage statistics</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🧠 Local Storage</h2>
  <p>If you choose to use the <em>history feature</em>, your recent coordinate inputs are saved <strong>locally on your device</strong>. This data never leaves your device and can be deleted at any time within the app.</p>

  <h2>🕵️ Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> share any data with third parties. There are no ads, analytics, trackers, or background network requests.</p>

  <h2>🧱 Permissions</h2>
  <p>Azimuth Finder does not request or use any special permissions beyond basic storage (if needed for future updates).</p>

  <h2>📬 Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this policy, contact: <a href="mailto:your@email.com">your@email.com</a></p>
